First, we focus on Scenario 1 with a less intensive supply of global radiation. It shows that the qualitative behavior is the same. For a low fossil energy price only the fossil solution exists, while at a specific point the two mixed solutions, with one being unstable and the other one being of saddle-type, occur and the areas of attraction are separated by an indifference threshold curve. However, a look on the price axis makes clear that remarkable changes concerning the position have happened. While the first bifurcation point at which these two additional mixed periodic solutions exists has been at pF=0.0446\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
